nodes.bodyText: Does ALL_IP_RANGES cover secondary ranges, even though this is empty?
nodes.diffHunk:
@@ -65,6 +65,11 @@ module "bastion_router" {
       name                     = module.private.subnets["${var.region}/${local.bastion_subnet_name}"].self_link
       source_ip_ranges_to_nat  = ["PRIMARY_IP_RANGE"]
       secondary_ip_range_names = []
+    },
+    {
+      name                     = module.private.subnets["${var.region}/${local.gke_clusters_subnet_name}"].self_link
+      source_ip_ranges_to_nat  = ["ALL_IP_RANGES"]
+      secondary_ip_range_names = []

nodes.bodyText: It does https://www.terraform.io/docs/providers/google/r/compute_router_nat.html. The reason why secondary_ip_range_names has to be also declared but left empty is because the router module currently always looks for it https://github.com/terraform-google-modules/terraform-google-cloud-router/blob/master/nat.tf
